description: ASML Holding NV loses its top spot as Europe's most valuable tech firm to SAP SE after a dramatic drop in market cap. This follows a disappointing guidance update and delays in chip plant construction. SAP's strong growth is propelled by increasing demand for cloud and AI solutions.
title: ASML loses Europe's top tech spot; here's new number1

description: Madhya Pradesh HC grants bail to Faizal, accused of anti-national slogans, with conditions that he reports to the police station twice a month. He must salute the national flag 21 times, reciting 'Bharat Mata Ki Jai' each time, until the trial concludes.
title: 'Bharat Mata ki jai' bail rider for 'Pak zindabad' sloganeer

description: Maharashtra's additional chief electoral officer Kiran Kulkarni stated that legal consultation is necessary before taking action on comments like 'vote jihad'. This follows deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis' controversial remark at a rally. The state electoral office hasn't received formal complaints since the model code of conduct was implemented on Tuesday.
title: Poll official: No complaint yet on 'vote jihad'

description: Congress is considering replicating Karnataka's 'five guarantees' promises for Maharashtra polls, including cash payments to women heads of households, free bus travel for women, free grains, free power, and unemployment allowance, with additional proposals like a caste census to address ongoing quota disputes.
title: Congress may pledge Karnataka-like '5 guarantees' in Maharashtra

description: The Maharashtra government retracts 112 government resolutions and a tourism tender following queries from the Chief Electoral Office about potential violations of the model code of conduct. The state is re-evaluating resolutions issued after election rules were enforced to ensure compliance.
title: Maharashtra nixes tender, 100 GRs issued after poll announced

description: Former One Direction singer Liam Payne, 31, tragically died after falling from a hotel balcony in Buenos Aires. The incident occurred at the Casa Sur Hotel, with local police suspecting he was under the influence. Payne had been open about his struggles with alcoholism and was reportedly sober for six months prior to the incident.
title: One Direction star Liam Payne dies at 31 after fall from hotel balcony

description: Uttarakhand DGP Abhinav Kumar ordered stricter food safety measures following incidents of adulteration and contamination, mandating employee verification and CCTV cameras in kitchens. Random inspections will be conducted, and street vendors will be monitored. Penalties for violations range up to Rs 1 lakh, supported by CM Pushkar Singh Dhami.
title: U'khand moves to stop 'spitting' in food, issues norms for eateries

description: A military couple, IAF Flight Lieutenant Deen Dayal Deep and Army Captain Renu Tanwar, were found dead in alleged suicides in Agra and Delhi. Capt Tanwar left a suicide note requesting joint cremation with her husband. Authorities are investigating, as both appeared untroubled beforehand. Family insights are awaited to uncover possible reasons.
title: IAF Fight Lieutenant, Captain wife die by suicide 250km apart

description: A helicopter carrying Chief Election Commissioner Rajiv Kumar made an emergency landing in Ralam village due to bad weather. The helicopter, en route to Milam Glacier, had diminished visibility and safely landed 35km from Munsiyari. All passengers, including Uttarakhand additional CEO Vijay Kumar Jogdande, are safe and awaiting weather clearance or will rest at a nearby ITBP camp.
title: CEC Rajiv Kumar's copter makes emergency landing

description: Sanjeev Sharma, an Indian-origin engineer at SpaceX, has gained viral attention for his pivotal role in developing a fully reusable rocket system, contributing to SpaceX's recent historic achievement of successfully capturing its Starship rocket's super heavy booster with the launch tower. His impressive career spans work with Indian Railways, Seagate, and significant contributions to NASA's lunar plans.
title: Linkedin profile of SpaceX principal engineer Sanjeev Sharma goes viral

description: Rajendra Bhavsar, a 64-year-old retired junior assistant, cleared NEET-UG without extensive preparation but aims for an MBBS seat next year. He secured admission for a BASLP course and remains determined to become a doctor. Data reveals many individuals above 30 attempt NEET, highlighting age is no barrier in pursuing medical dreams.
title: ‘Dream to be Dr:’ Retired roadways employee writes NEET, qualifies for physio
Activist saves snake with mouth-to-mouth resuscitation

description: At MP's Barwani district hospital, a black magic practitioner was summoned to perform rituals on a snakebite victim despite medical treatment being underway. The hospital administration has issued a showcause notice to the nurse involved for not preventing the unconventional intervention. The victim, Rakesh, eventually recovered.
title: Black magic on snake-bitten man in MP hospital

description: Canadian PM Justin Trudeau reiterated accusations against India for the killing of pro-Khalistan terrorist Hardeep Singh Nijjar, despite lacking substantial evidence. He testified before the Foreign Interference Commission, highlighting sovereignty concerns and defending separatists' freedom of expression, though Canada has not shared concrete proof with India.
title: Had no proof, only intel when we first accused India: Justin Trudeau

description: NCDRC orders Railways to compensate nearly Rs 4.7 lakh to a passenger for stolen luggage on the Amarkantak Express in 2017. The commission stated that Railways failed in their duty to prevent unauthorized entry into the reserved coach, dismissing their defense under Section 100 of the Railway Act.
title: Railways told to pay Rs 4.7 lakh to passenger for bag theft

description: The UK’s FCDO backs Canada amid the diplomatic row over allegations involving Indian officials in criminal activities, including the murder of separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar. India's response includes expelling diplomats, while the row impacts India-Canada relations with accusations lacking concrete evidence.
title: London sides with Ottawa in diplomatic row with India

description: The Supreme Court of India sentenced a man to 20 years in prison for strangling his nine-month pregnant daughter in 2013 for marrying a lower caste individual. His death sentence was reduced, considering his good conduct in jail. The conviction was supported by his wife's testimony about his anger over the inter-caste marriage.
title: Honour killing case: SC cuts death to life term
'Hooch' claims 12 lives in Bihar; 2 held

description: An 18-year-old girl was found dead with acid burns on her face in Krishnanagar, West Bengal. The victim's fiance was arrested following allegations from her parents, who suspect gang rape and murder. Authorities are awaiting the post mortem report.
title: 18-yr-old found dead with acid burns in Bengal, fiance arrested

description: Lobbying has resumed in Haryana Congress as 31 out of 37 newly-elected MLAs gather at former CM Hooda's residence ahead of selecting their new leader. Five MLAs associated with MP Selja boycotted the meeting. The Congress is rumored to consider a non-Jat candidate for CLP leader, with calls for Panchkula MLA Chander Mohan emerging from the anti-Hooda faction.
title: It's Hooda vs Selja again before election of Haryana CLP

description: Prashant Kishor's Jan Suraaj Party has nominated Lt Gen Krishna Singh as its candidate for the Tarari assembly bypoll in Bihar. Singh is the only vice chief of army staff from Bihar besides the late S K Sinha. Prashant Kishor also mentioned that the party would announce candidates for three other assembly seats shortly.
title: PK fields Army ex-vice chief Krishna Singh for Bihar bypoll

description: Nayab Singh Saini is set to be sworn in as Haryana CM on Valmiki Jayanti, a date chosen by PM Modi symbolically acknowledging Dalit support. Home minister Amit Shah declared Saini as BJP legislature party leader, with Anil Vij’s endorsement despite previous contention over the post.
title: Nayab Singh Saini gets backing of Haryana MLAs, to take oath as CM today

description: The Delhi HC has ordered Wikipedia to remove a page criticizing a prior court decision within 36 hours, deeming it 'prima facie contemptuous.' The page commented on a directive for Wikipedia to disclose user details behind alleged defamatory edits. HC noted the site's discussion of court observations compounded the contempt.
title: Remove page on earlier order in 36 hrs, Delhi HC tells Wikipedia

description: In Chhattisgarh, the police arrested NSUI district president Chandrakant Chaudhary and three others following the capture of Kuldeep Sahu, who confessed to killing a constable's wife and daughter. Despite finding the bodies nude, medical reports showed no signs of sexual assault. Kuldeep’s house is being demolished for being illegal.
title: NSUI neta held for murder of Chhattisgarh cop's wife, daughter
In West Bengal hospital, 9 twin pairs born in 24 hrs

description: The government has approved an increase in the Minimum Support Price (MSP) for six rabi crops ahead of the winter sowing season, with significant hikes for mustard, rapeseed, lentil, and wheat. The move aims to ensure remunerative prices for farmers and encourage crop diversification.
title: MSP for 6 rabi crops hiked ahead of sowing season

description: The son of a DMK functionary, who had been missing since Saturday, was found dead on a neighbouring farm in Vellore. The family suspects foul play due to their complaints about illegal sand mining. Police are investigating the case, considering both accidental and suspicious death aspects.
title: DMK neta's son found dead, family blames sand mafia

description: K Marigowda resigned as chairman of Mysore Urban Development Authority citing health issues and following Chief Minister Siddaramaiah's request. He emphasized loyalty to the CM and denied stepping down due to the ongoing investigation related to the allotment of residential sites to the CM's wife.
title: Muda chief, an aide of Sidda, quits citing health grounds

description: Focus on cricket as PCB chief greets EAM
title: No bilateral but India, Pak ‘break the ice’ with Jaishankar visit

description: Combating terrorism, extremism, and separatism is vital for the SCO's growth and integration. External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar emphasized cooperation based on mutual respect and sovereignty. Jaishankar also stressed the importance of reforming the UN Security Council to make it more representative and accountable. India remains firm on respecting sovereignty, standing against China’s BRI.
title: SCO must root out terrorism, respect territorial integrity: Jaishankar

description: The US Navy is searching for two aviators after an EA-18G Growler jet crashed during a routine flight near Mount Rainier. The incident, under investigation, saw search teams sent despite adverse weather. The aircraft from Whidbey Island is renowned for its advanced electronic warfare capabilities and functions as a critical defense line.
title: US Navy jet with two onboard crashes, search operation under way

description: The Congress party urged the Indian government to engage the opposition in addressing rising tensions with Canada, emphasizing national unity and transparency. They stressed the shared responsibility of protecting India's global reputation amidst serious allegations by the US and Canada against India. Diplomatic expulsions have ensued.
title: 'Necessary for entire country to... ': Congress on India-Canada diplomatic fallout

description: Bengaluru faced heavy rainfall leading to severe flooding at Manyata Tech Park, submerging vehicles and streets. Viral videos showed floodwaters crashing down walls and perilous conditions for commuters. Social media reactions highlighted concerns over the tech park's location near Nagawara Lake and the city's inadequate flood management.
title: 'Nadi paar karke aate the' & other viral posts after Bengaluru flooding
Mobile phones not allowed inside polling booths in Mumbai while voting: Poll official

description: England opener Ben Duckett broke the record for the fastest 2,000 Test runs by balls faced during the second Test against Pakistan in Multan. Duckett achieved the milestone in just 2,293 deliveries, surpassing Tim Southee’s previous record. Despite his century, England faced a middle-order collapse, ending the day at 239/6.
title: New Record! Eng opener Duckett becomes fastest to...

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau admitted that accusations against India in Khalistani extremist Hardeep Singh Nijjar's killing were based on weak intelligence, not solid evidence. This coincides with Khalistani terrorist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun’s claim of sharing information with Trudeau’s office, deepening the bilateral rift.
title: 'No hard proof when we made first allegation ... ': Trudeau now admits amid diplomatic row with India

description: Elon Musk, despite being born in South Africa and constitutionally ineligible for the presidency, has become a key figure in Trump's 2024 campaign, using his influence and financial support. His involvement sees him clashing with Kamala Harris in a crucial battleground state, Pennsylvania.
title: Starship Musk to Trump's rescue as Elon goes full MAGA

description: Reliance Industries (RIL) has set the record date for its 1:1 bonus share issue. Post-issue, RIL's authorized share capital will rise to Rs 50,000 crore. Shareholders will see their shares double, enhancing stock liquidity without changing the total investment value.
title: Ambani-led Reliance Industries sets record date for 1:1 bonus share

description: Persistent rain canceled Day 1 of the first Test between India and New Zealand at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru. No toss or play was possible. Weather forecasts predict more rain and thunderstorms, potentially affecting Day 2. India aims to secure a series win while New Zealand seeks recovery after recent defeats.
title: Will rain play spoilsport on Day 2 of IND vs NZ?

description: BJP's Devendra Fadnavis challenged Sharad Pawar to declare MVA's CM candidate for the November 20 assembly elections. Hinting at Eknath Shinde for Mahayuti's CM, Fadnavis evaded a direct reply. Uddhav Thackeray urged allies to announce MVA's candidate, emphasizing unity for Maharashtra’s interest. The Congress and NCP remain cautious, preferring to wait for election results.
title: Suspense over 'CM face' in Mahayuti and MVA as Maharashtra gears up for battle of ballots

description: Amazon Prime Video plans to introduce ads for its Indian viewers in 2024, similar to its US model. While an ad-free option will be available, pricing details are yet to be disclosed.
title: Amazon may bring US subscription model for Prime Video to India

description: Both Meghan Markle and Kate Middleton were seen without their engagement rings in recent appearances. Kate's missing ring signifies milestones with Prince William, while Meghan's absence of her ring fuels speculation about her marital issues with Prince Harry, as they pursue separate professional paths.  Meghan's engagement rings underwent several changes since it was first given to her by Prince Harry in 2017.
title: Meghan Markle's missing engagement ring more significant than Kate's because...

description: Senior directors of a Pakistan college refuted claims of a student rape on campus, amidst widespread protests fueled by social media posts. "The incident does not exist. I will resign and I will leave this profession and stand with the students if the incident took place," said the Lahore college director. Maryam Nawaz, the CM of Pakistan's Punjab also addressed the alleged rape incident, asserting that the accusations were 'baseless and fabricated'.
title: 'Incident doesn't exist': Pak college denies campus rape claim amid protest

description: At least seven more flights received hoax threat messages, disrupting nearly 20 in the last three days. Authorities are intensifying efforts to track and prosecute the perpetrators. Enhanced security, including sky marshals, has been deployed, and a minor has been arrested for his alleged involvement in multiple threats.
title: Aviation minister on flight bomb hoaxes: Minor arrested, others responsible to be duly prosecuted

description: Valmiki Jayanti 2024, observed on October 17, honors Maharishi Valmiki, the revered author of the Ramayana. Celebrated with fervor, the day involves decorations, prayers, and feeding the underprivileged. Legend recounts Valmiki's transformation from a robber named Ratnakar to a sage under Narada's guidance. This day holds special significance in North India.
title: Valmiki Jayanti 2024: Date, Time, Story, Significance and Celebration

description: Uber CEO Dara Khosrowshahi acknowledges the competitive challenge posed by Elon Musk in self-driving cars but is open to collaborating with Tesla. He highlights Tesla's technology and the potential for partnership. Uber's future strategies could include direct competition, collaboration, or a combination, depending on Tesla's moves. Uber has existing partnerships with Waymo and Cruise.
title: Competing with Elon Musk not easy, says Uber CEO

description: Taylor Swift announced on Good Morning America she will release 'The Official Eras Tour Book' after her tour ends in December 2024. The 256-page book will include personal reflections and behind-the-scenes photos. Physical copies explaining her album 'The Tortured Poets Department's anthology' will also be available at Target.
title: Taylor Swift to release her first official book. Read all about it

description: However, ABC News has dismissed the Harris campaign's suggestion that Trump experienced a "senior moment" on stage, instead highlighting how well he managed the situation. The broadcaster reported that Trump had decided to change the course of the rally after two of his supporters encountered medical issues during the event in Oaks, Pennsylvania.
title: Did Harris share fake news about Trump's 'senior moment'?

description: Sahana, widow of Renukaswamy who was allegedly murdered by actor Darshan Thoogudeepa, gave birth to a healthy baby boy. Thanking the hospital and doctors for providing free treatment, Renukaswamy's father, Kashinath Shivanagoudar, expressed his emotional response to the reporters and said, "Felt happy as though my son had come back." Renukaswamy was killed after reportedly sending obscene messages to Pavithra Gowda, wife of actor Darshan.
title: 'Son has come back': Father of actor Darshan's victim welcomes grandson

description: Hungary's government is considering halting new Airbnb licences and increasing taxes on short-term rentals in Budapest due to concerns over housing prices and the city's character.
title: One of most popular tourist cities in Europe may freeze Airbnb licences
Union minister Suresh Gopi seeks bail in alleged journalist misconduct case

description: CISF officials at Delhi's IGI Airport detained a Mumbai-bound traveler for possessing a 5.56 mm bullet in his baggage without proper authorization. The incident occurred during security checks, resulting in the passenger being removed from his Indigo flight and handed over to Delhi Police for further investigation.
title: Passenger arrested at Delhi airport for carrying bullet in luggage

description: Miami Dolphins quarterback Tua Tagovailoa's return in Week 8 is uncertain despite progress reports, with some analysts advising rest for the season. Mike Florio and Dan Patrick hold contrasting views on his health decisions. Tagovailoa's potential return sparks debate among Dolphins fans, amid ongoing scrutiny since his initial concussion.
title: Mike Florio’s conflicting views on Miami Dolphins quarterback Tua Tagovailoa’s health

description: Mumbai police issued notices to a teenage boy, his father, and another individual from Rajnandgaon in Chhattisgarh for social media bomb threats that disrupted three international flights. An Air India flight was diverted to New Delhi, and two IndiGo flights faced delays for security checks. The investigation was triggered by the bomb threat, which prompted an immediate response from law enforcement.
title: Hoax bomb threat: Teenage boy, father under probe for targeting Mumbai planes

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad are set to invest heavily in retaining key players such as Heinrich Klaasen for Rs 23 crore and Pat Cummins for Rs 18 crore ahead of the IPL mega auction. Abhishek Sharma will be retained at Rs 14 crore; Travis Head and Nitish Kumar Reddy may also continue in the franchise, an ESPNcricinfo report said.
title: IPL: SRH set to shell out Rs 23 crore to retain...
'Felt incomplete ... ': What Rahul Gandhi said after Omar Abdullah's CM oath

description: Khalistani terrorist Gurpatwant Singh Pannun revealed that Sikh for Justice has been communicating with Canadian PM Trudeau's office, sharing information against India. This comes amid escalating tensions between India and Canada after allegations of India's involvement in the killing of Hardeep Singh Nijjar, which India denies. Both nations have expelled each other's diplomats. ​​It also accused Canada of giving space to extremist and anti-India elements in their country.
title: Pannun says he shared information against India with Trudeau's office

description: Binance has helped the Delhi Police in dismantling a scam run by 'M/s Goldcoat Solar,' resulting in several arrests and the seizure of over 100,000 USDT. The scam deceived users into investing in a fake solar energy project by impersonating officials using fake SIM cards.
title: Binance helps Delhi Police bust another crypto scam

description: Over 100 people lost their lives and at least 50 were injured when a petro tanker exploded in Majiya village, Nigeria. The tanker was traveling from Portharcourt to Nguru and overturned, causing a spill that ignited. Villagers collecting the fuel perished in the ensuing fire, according to the Jigawa police.
title: Over 100 killed, 50 injured in fuel tanker explosion in Nigeria

description: AB de Villiers responded warmly to Virat Kohli’s congratulatory letter on his induction into the ICC Hall of Fame. Kohli praised de Villiers as the 'absolute number one' and recounted their memorable partnership at RCB. De Villiers thanked Kohli for the kind words, illustrating their deep bond and mutual respect. Other inductees include Sir Alastair Cook and Neetu David.
title: ABD calls Kohli 'my biscuit' in reply to letter, says...
'Dance of death': Bengal guv on Mamata govt's Durga Puja carnival amid doctors' protest

description: Former India captain Anil Kumble recommends KL Rahul to open in the first Test against Australia if Rohit Sharma is unavailable, keeping Shubman Gill at No. 3 given his adaptability in different positions. The former India head coach highlights Gill's previous success in Australia and emphasizes the importance of maintaining the team balance.
title: Kumble wants this player to open in Oz in Rohit's absence

description: In Anand Vihar, a man named Nirala was killed by his friend Ankit following a dispute over Rs 400 for liquor. Ankit assaulted Nirala with a brick and tried to avoid capture by checking into a de-addiction center. Police, after reviewing extensive CCTV footage, apprehended Ankit, who confessed and stated he used the stolen money for more alcohol.
title: 'Beaten with bricks': Man kills friend after dispute over Rs 400 for liquor

description: A recent report titled Happiness at Work - How Happy is India's Workforce? - 2024 reveals alarming trends, indicating that 70% of Indian employees are unhappy in their workplaces. Conducted by The Happiest Places to Work and the Happiness Research Academy, the study analyzed responses from 2,000 individuals across various sectors. Key findings highlight significant age, gender, and regional disparities in workplace satisfaction, with over half of the workforce considering resignation. The pressing concern underscores the importance of supportive work environments, suggesting that innovative policies, like 'unhappy leave,' could help address mental health concerns and improve overall employee well-being.
title: 'Unhappy leave' in China: A solution for India's dissatisfied workforce?

description: External Affairs Minister Jaishankar concluded his two-day visit to Pakistan, expressing gratitude for the hospitality received at the SCO meeting. He signed eight outcome documents and emphasized India's constructive role in deliberations. This visit marks the first time in nearly nine years that an Indian foreign minister has traveled to Pakistan, amid ongoing tensions.
title: EAM Jaishankar wraps up Pak visit, thanks Shehbaz, SCO hosts for 'hospitality'

description: Elon Musk’s Tesla has unveiled the Cybercab, a fully self-driving vehicle with no driver, pedals, or steering wheel, showcasing the future of urban transport. The much-anticipated reveal took place at California’s Warner Bros. Discovery studios, where the Cybercab navigated a controlled, artificial city environment. Although not yet ready for public roads, the event sparked excitement and raised important questions about the potential and challenges of autonomous technology. The Cybercab offers a glimpse into the future of mobility, but its readiness and safety for real-world conditions remain to be seen.
title: Inside Elon Musk's fully self-driving Tesla Cybercab

description: AB de Villiers, Alastair Cook and Neetu David are the latest inductees into the ICC Hall of Fame. De Villiers accumulated over 20,000 international runs for South Africa. Cook, England's all-time leading Test run-scorer, retired with 12,472 Test runs. David, the second Indian woman to be inducted, claimed 141 ODI wickets.
title: De Villiers, Cook, David inducted in ICC Hall of Fame

description: A recent National Statistical Office survey reveals that less than one-third of individuals aged 15-29 in India can effectively browse the internet, send emails, and conduct online transactions. This digital divide significantly impacts education quality, particularly in rural areas. The article explores the role of the internet in enhancing educational access, the necessity for digital skills in a competitive global environment, and the stark regional disparities affecting students' learning opportunities.
title: Only 26.8% youth have internet skills: Could this affect quality education?

description: This article evaluates the hype surrounding five WWE female superstars, including Liv Morgan, Nia Jax, Chelsea Green, Tiffany Stratton, and Naomi. Despite their apparent popularity and achievements, the author questions whether their current roles, performances, and storylines truly justify the attention they receive from fans and the wrestling community.
title: 5 most overrated WWE female superstars of 2024

description: The global star Priyanka Chopra Jonas who is currently gearing up for Russo Brothers' Citadel season two, has arrived in India, and was snapped at the Mumbai airport.
title: Priyanka Chopra greets paps as she arrives in India: Watch

description: Nasser Hussain criticized Pakistan captain Shan Masood's field placements during England's second Test innings in Multan, especially against Ben Duckett. He pointed out Masood's lack of preparation for Duckett's predictable sweeps, suggesting proactive positioning to limit scoring opportunities. Hussain contrasted this with Pat Cummins' strategic planning during the Ashes, highlighting the importance of pre-game readiness.
title: 'Looked completely lost': Hussain blasts Pak captain

description: Sunil Mittal, chairman of Bharti Airtel, lauded Prime Minister Narendra Modi's vision and affirmed Airtel's commitment to innovation and social responsibility.
title: IMC 2024: Bharti Airtel chairman Sunil Mittal makes this 'promise' to PM Narendra Modi

description: Arvind Kejriwal criticizes BJP, claiming his imprisonment was due to their insecurity over his effective governance in Delhi. He alleges attempts to halt his work and life-threatening treatment in jail. Kejriwal warns that BJP's potential control in Delhi could end public benefits and harm schools and hospitals.
title: 'If you vote for BJP ...': Kejriwal warns Delhi voters ahead of assembly elections

description: The Central Government has approved a significant increase in the Minimum Support Prices for six Rabi crops for the 2025-26 marketing season to ensure farmers' profitability. Wheat's MSP is set at Rs 2,425 per quintal, with rapeseed & mustard seeing the highest increment of Rs 300 per quintal. The announcement was made by union minister Ashwini Vaishnaw.
title: Centre approves MSP for 6 Rabi crops for marketing season 2025-26

description: The Hunter's Moon will rise tonight, peaking on October 17, 2024. For capturing this celestial event with a smartphone, tips include finding an open location, using a tripod for stability, avoiding flash, manual focusing, enabling HDR mode, and using optical zoom. Subtle editing and time-lapse features can enhance the final images.
title: Supermoon visible in India on Oct 16, 17, 18: Simple tips to take moon photos with phone
'No traffic stoppage for me': Omar Abdullah's first order as J&K CM

description: Virat Kohli hailed AB de Villiers as the 'absolute number one' on his ICC Hall of Fame induction, highlighting their shared cricketing journey, De Villiers' unmatched talent and belief, and his impactful contributions to the game. Sir Alastair Cook and Neetu David also join the Hall of Fame Class of 2024.
title: Kohli hails 'No.1' ABD on induction in ICC Hall of Fame

description: The Supreme Court has asked Delhi's lieutenant governor VK Saxena to file an affidavit on actions taken against those responsible for felling nearly 1,100 trees in Delhi's Ridge area for road widening. The court seeks clarification on permission discussions, timing of LG's awareness about the need for permission, and measures taken against the erring officers.
title: 'LG must act before ... ': SC on felling of trees in Delhi's Ridge area

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi's cabinet has approved a new rail-cum-road bridge over the river Ganga in Varanasi. With four railway lines and a six-lane highway, the bridge will drastically improve transport capacity.
title: ‘One of the biggest…’: New rail-road bridge in Varanasi approved

description: The first day of the India-New Zealand Test in Bengaluru was rained out due to heavy rain over the past 48 hours. Umpires called off play at 2:30 pm. Practices were canceled, and the toss is now scheduled for Thursday morning. Tests in Pune and Mumbai follow this match.
title: India vs New Zealand, 1st Test: Rain washes out Day 1

description: Amid a rise in hoax threats targeting commercial flights, the Indian government is working to add people issuing such threats to the no-fly list. Airlines are urging for prompt action as these threats disrupt schedules and incur significant costs. Authorities assure zero risk in flying and are tracing the culprits for strict legal action.
title: Threat messages for flights: 'Working on putting them on no fly list,' says govt

description: In 2016, Virat Kohli scored a double century against New Zealand, leading India to a significant win in the Test series. Kohli's 211-run innings included a 365-run partnership with Ajinkya Rahane, contributing to India's commanding total. India won the series 3-0, and R. Ashwin's stellar performance earned him Player of the Series.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli’s finest innings vs New Zealand in Tests

description: An Akasa Air flight to Bengaluru returned to Delhi after a bomb threat, with 174 passengers on board. The airline's emergency teams advised the pilot to divert to Indira Gandhi International Airport as a precaution. This incident follows recent bomb threats received by four planes, causing security drills at various airports.
title: Bengaluru-bound Akasa Air flight returns to Delhi after bomb threat

description: Anil Kumble lauds Rohit Sharma's leadership in Test cricket, commending his proactive tactics and effective handling of young talents like Shubman Gill and Yashasvi Jaiswal. He also praises Rohit's utilization of key bowlers such as Ravichandran Ashwin, Ravindra Jadeja, and Jasprit Bumrah, highlighting the skipper's ability to marshal resources and navigate team dynamics.
title: 'Rohit Sharma has been...': Anil Kumble on India captain's leadership

description: The Israeli military uncovered a sophisticated, well-equipped tunnel in South Lebanon allegedly used by Hezbollah operatives. This tunnel, unlike those in Gaza, includes operational rooms, ammunition, and food supplies, demonstrating advanced preparation for potential attacks on Israeli northern communities.
title: 'AK-47 rifles, a bedroom': Israel shares video of tunnel in Lebanon

description: A remote-controlled explosive device detonated near a police vehicle in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa’s Buner district, injuring at least five officers, including a severely wounded sub-inspector. This attack comes on the heels of another recent terrorist assault by the TTP in Bannu district, which killed four police officers.
title: Bomb blast in Pakistan's Buner amidst SCO meet, 5 police officers injured

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar emphasized the importance of adhering to the SCO's charter amidst current global disruptions like conflicts and climate change at the SCO council meeting in Islamabad. He urged steadfast commitment to combating terrorism, separatism, and extremism while fostering cooperation to boost trade, connectivity, and industrial competitiveness among member states.
title: 'Terrorism unlikely to encourage trade': Top quotes from Jaishankar's speech in Pakistan

description: Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis stated that the Mahayuti alliance doesn't need to announce its CM candidate as their leader is already present. He challenged the MVA to declare their candidate, criticized their past governance, and highlighted Mahayuti's achievements and election plans.
title: 'Sitting here': Fadnavis hints at Mahayuti's CM face ahead of polls

description: K Marigowda, Chairman of MUDA and Siddaramaiah’s close aide, resigns amid allegations of land allotment irregularities involving Siddaramaiah’s wife. The opposition accuses the Karnataka chief minister of misconduct, with calls for his resignation growing louder.
title: 'CM instructed me to resign': MUDA chief quits amid land scam allegations

description: Shooters involved in the killing of NCP leader Baba Siddique trained using YouTube videos and practiced at a rented house in Mumbai's Kurla area. Key suspect Shivkumar Gautam, on the run, trained accomplices Gurmail Singh and Dharmaraj Kashyap for the shooting. They communicated via social media apps to avoid surveillance.
title: Baba Siddique murder: How shooters learnt to operate guns through YouTube videos

description: Virat Kohli, prioritizing winning over stats, poses a significant threat to opponents, as his focus on team victory naturally leads to big scores, says Mike Hesson. Hesson believes Kohli's ability to maintain tempo and counter-attack is crucial, especially in Australian conditions, predicting strong performances despite his recent low scores in Bangladesh.
title: Virat Kohli's Test form at 'a dangerous stage': Here's why

description: Blinkit introduces a 10-minute return and exchange service for clothing and footwear in select Indian cities to address size and fit concerns. Initially tested in Delhi NCR, the service is now available in Mumbai, Bangalore, Hyderabad, and Pune, with more cities to follow soon.
title: Blinkit takes on Myntra, Ajio & other fashion websites with this '10-minute service'

description: Rain delayed the start of India vs New Zealand Test match in Bengaluru, washing out the first session and even not allowing the toss to happen. The series spans three matches, with the next two Tests in in Pune and Mumbai respecively, which will be followed by India's tour to Australia for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.
title: Virat's swag under a hoodie steals the thunder in Bengaluru - see pic

description: Starlink CEO Elon Musk expressed gratitude for India's decision to allocate satcomm spectrum administratively rather than through auction, following union telecom minister Jyotiraditya Scindia's announcement.
title: Elon Musk after telecom minister denies spectrum auction: 'Much appreciated...'

description: Nayab Singh Saini is set to be sworn in as Haryana CM for a second term on October 17 in Panchkula, with PM Modi and senior BJP leaders attending. The event highlights BJP's consideration of southern Haryana's contribution to its recent election victory, potentially assigning a significant role to the region, pending approval from Modi and Amit Shah.
title: Nayab Singh Saini to be sworn in as Haryana CM for second term

description: The Supreme Court criticized Punjab and Haryana for inadequate action on stubble burning, summoning their chief secretaries for non-compliance. The court termed the Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) as a 'toothless tiger' and directed penal action against state officers. Punjab's failure to seek financial aid for farmers to address the issue was also highlighted.
title: Stubble burning: SC slams Haryana, Punjab, summons chief secretaries

description: DA hike news: Central government employees and pensioners receive early Diwali cheer with PM Modi-led Union Cabinet approving a dearness allowance hike, effective January 2024.
title: DA hike: Diwali comes early for central govt employees

description: Former President Trump accused Google of bias, claiming it only shows negative stories about him. He spoke with Google CEO Sundar Pichai about the issue, suggesting the company is rigged. Trump remains critical of Google but wary of breaking it up, noting its power and impact compared to China.
title: Donald Trump: I called Google CEO Sundar Pichai the other day and said ...

description: The suspected shooters of NCP politician Baba Siddique, who was killed outside his son's office, made over 10 unsuccessful attempts previously. Police arrested an additional suspect, Harishkumar Nishad, linking him to earlier arrested individuals and the Lawrence Bishnoi gang. A motorcycle for reconnaissance, funded by Praveen Lonkar, was used in the plot.
title: Baba Siddique murder: Suspects made 10 attempts on NCP leader's life in past month

description: Filmmaker Ram Gopal Varma has stirred a social media buzz by calling gangster Lawrence Bishnoi 'good looking' while commenting on the ongoing case involving Bishnoi's gang and the murder of politician Baba Siddiqui. Varma also urged Salman Khan to counter Bishnoi's threat and shared a satirical take on the legal and criminal drama unfolding around the case.
title: RGV calls Lawrence Bishnoi 'good looking'; netizens ask him to direct gangster's biopic

description: Blinkit introduces a 10-minute return and exchange service for clothing and footwear in select Indian cities to address size and fit concerns. Initially tested in Delhi NCR, the service is now available in Mumbai, Bangalore, Hyderabad, and Pune, with more cities to follow soon.
title: Blinkit launches 10-minute returns service in these cities

description: President Mohamed Muizzu announced the removal of 228 political appointees from Maldives' government ministries to reduce expenditure as part of the Economic Reform Agenda. The move aims to save money monthly and streamline operations. Muizzu has also been fostering economic reforms and enhancing collaboration with India, encouraging investment in sustainable ventures.
title: Cash-strapped Maldives removes 228 govt appointees to cut costs

description: Mayank Kumar, co-founder and managing director of Upgrad, has resigned to launch a new venture focusing on Blue Collar and Global Talent Mobility. Kumar’s departure coincides with Ronnie Screwvala increasing his active role, as Upgrad nears $50-$60 million in funding at a $2.25 billion valuation.
title: Upgrad MD Mayank Kumar resigns; Here’s what he wrote in the internal note

description: This apart, Salman Khan's personal security has also been beefed up, and it was reported that he has been advised not to entertain any visitors for the next few weeks. However, a close family friend of the actor told ETimes that Salman khan's doors have always been open for friends and colleagues of the film industry
title: Vivek Oberoi's old speech praising the community goes viral

description: Kamran Ghulam hit a century on debut against England, replacing Babar Azam in the Pakistan team. Despite a stellar run in domestic cricket, Ghulam's international opportunities had been limited. His century brought attention, as did a viral video of an incident where Haris Rauf slapped him during a PSL match for dropping a catch.
title: Watch: When Haris Rauf slapped Kamran Ghulam in a PSL match

description: Elon Musk commits to serving India through Starlink, following the government's decision to allocate satellite spectrum administratively. This move sets up competition with Reliance Jio and Bharti Airtel, with Starlink expected to receive a GMPCS license soon.
title: ‘Will do the best to serve…’: Elon Musk to Jyotiraditya Scindia’s comments

description: Omar Abdullah has been sworn in as the chief minister of Jammu and Kashmir, leading the first government after Article 370 abrogation. The ceremony at SKICC saw leaders like Rahul Gandhi and Priyanka Gandhi Vadra attend. Congress opted not to join the ministry immediately, still advocating for Jammu and Kashmir's statehood restoration.
title: Omar Abdullah takes oath as J&K CM, Congress to stay out of govt

description: Advocate Gunaratna Sadavarte leaves Bigg Boss 18 due to an urgent legal matter. He clarifies that he was not eliminated but needed to be present for a crucial court case involving his wife. Sadavarte reflects on his unique journey and audience admiration.
title: BB18: Gunaratna Sadavarte exits from show; says 'I'm not a reel star'

description: Vidya Balan and Kartik Aaryan join Kaun Banega Crorepati 16, adding humor and charm to the show. Vidya teases a nervous Kartik before they settle in with Amitabh Bachchan. They also playfully reference their movie roles, making the episode even more entertaining.
title: KBC16: Vidya Balan takes a fun test of Kartik Aaryan before entering the show

description: Sharad Purnima, observed on October 16, 2024, marks the harvest season and is ideal for spiritual rituals. Each zodiac sign can perform specific manifesting activities during the full moon, ranging from candle rituals for Aries to dream manifestation for Pisces, enhancing their unique energies and intentions.
title: Sharad Purnima 2024: Manifesting magic for every zodiac sign

description: Mikhail Pichugin survived over two months adrift in the Sea of Okhotsk, after his boat, intended for a whale-watching trip, went off course. The ordeal claimed the lives of his brother and 15-year-old nephew. Rescuers discovered Pichugin, severely weakened, after drifting approximately 1,000 kilometers from the starting point.
title: Watch: Russian survives over two months in inflatable boat on icy sea water

description: A Delhi-bound IndiGo flight from Mumbai was diverted to Ahmedabad due to a bomb threat, later confirmed as a hoax. Nearly 200 passengers were on the plane, which landed safely at Ahmedabad airport. Following a thorough overnight check, nothing suspicious was found. Similar threats affected multiple flights recently, including international ones.
title: IndiGo Mumbai-Delhi flight diverted to Ahmedabad after bomb threat

description: Currently, there aren't many details available about this motorcycle. The RE electric bike will officially debut on November 4th in Milan, Italy, and will also be featured at the 2024 EICMA motorcycle show. It’s expected to be named the Royal Enfield Classic Electric, or possibly revive the Electra name
title: Royal Enfield electric motorcycle teased: Launch, features, and more

description: The US has warned Israel it might withhold military aid if Israel doesn't improve humanitarian aid delivery to Gaza within 30 days. This follows concerns over the deteriorating conditions in Gaza, highlighted in a letter from US officials Antony Blinken and Lloyd Austin. The US urges Israel to increase aid trucks and open more crossings.
title: US tells Israel to improve Gaza humanitarian situation or risk military aid

description: Pakistan A captain Mohammad Haris reveals his team is banned from discussing India in the dressing room ahead of their Emerging Teams Asia Cup opener. Haris emphasizes the need to focus on all teams and avoid undue pressure from overthinking about their match against India. He said they have to respect other opponents as well.
title: 'Banned from talking about India': Pakistan A captain reveals

description: In response to emergency calls due to severe weather, V Govindarajan's team of 25 volunteers in Tambaram Corporation has turned his home into a call centre to assist residents. Collectively, they are coordinating relief efforts, logging complaints, and seeking help from officials, despite jammed helplines.
title: Chennai flood crisis: When helplines fail, residents step up

description: In December of last year, five friends, including siblings, took a memorable photograph at a village wedding in Bahraich, UP. Now, ten months later, two of them, Shivkumar Gautam and Dharmaraj Kashyap, have been implicated in the murder of Baba Siddique in Mumbai, with Dharmaraj arrested and Shivkumar still at large.
title: 'Shooting Stars': Bahraich buddies awash in Baba Siddique murder infamy
Canada using a routine NIA post to link India to goon's killing in Winnipeg

description: Continuous rains in Bengaluru have delayed the toss for the first Test between India and New Zealand. The 'SubAir' system at M Chinnaswamy Stadium is crucial in managing wet conditions, ensuring the pitch is ready swiftly after rain stops. With weather forecast for more disruptions over the next few days, the state-of-the-art drainage system will have a major role to play.
title: How Bengaluru stadium drainage system may save Ind-NZ Test

description: KITS has advised IT, BT, and private companies in Bengaluru to allow employees to work from home on October 16, 2024, due to expected heavy rain and an orange alert. Inclement weather has already caused severe flooding in areas like Yelahanka and Mahadevapura, affecting homes and disrupting traffic. Residents are frustrated with inadequate waterlogging solutions.
title: Bengaluru rain: IT, BT firms asked to allow work from home today

description: Late industrialist Ratan Tata praised then Prime Minister PV Narasimha Rao in 1996 for his significant role in initiating economic reforms in India, expressing admiration and gratitude for Rao's far-sighted efforts that transformed India's economy and placed it on the global economic map.
title: 'Felt compelled to write to you ... ': Ratan Tata’s 1996 letter to Narasimha Rao

description: Opposition parties in India urge the government to engage them in addressing the diplomatic crisis with Canada following the killing of Sikh separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar. They stress the need for transparency, unified action, and diplomacy to manage escalating tensions.
title: 'Never used to happen earlier': How oppn reacted to India-Canada row

description: External Affairs Minister Dr. S Jaishankar visited Islamabad for the SCO Council of Heads of Government summit. During his visit, Jaishankar took a morning walk and planted a sapling at the Indian High Commission premises. This marks the first visit by an Indian foreign minister to Pakistan in nearly nine years, highlighting India's commitment to the SCO.
title: Jaishankar takes a stroll at IHC in Pakistan, plants sapling; see pics

description: Omar Abdullah, the chief minister-elect of Jammu and Kashmir, reaffirms the strength of the NC-Congress alliance, dismissing rift rumors. Abdullah clarifies that ministerial positions remain open for Congress as talks continue. The alliance is set to establish the first elected government since the abrogation of Article 370.
title: No cabinet berths for Congress in J&K? Omar Abdullah responds

description: Prashant Jamdade from Sangli, Maharashtra, won Rs 25,00,000 on Kaun Banega Crorepati 16. Bachchu Santra from Hooghly, West Bengal, became the next contestant, shared humorous anecdotes, and secured Rs 1,60,000 before quitting. The episode featured light-hearted moments and challenging questions.
title: KBC16: Big B expresses his happiness while talking about 'Mohun Bagan'

description: Amid protests, Indore's Government Mahatma Gandhi Memorial Medical College was purified with Ganga water after an alleged Halloween party defaced a historic building. The college denied permitting such an event, while doctors demanded action against those responsible. Disturbing graffiti and images were found on the walls, igniting calls for preservation of the site's historical significance.
title: Doctors cleanse medical college building with Gangajal after 'Halloween party'

description: The diplomatic crisis between India and Canada worsens as Canada accuses India of involvement in the killing of Sikh separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar. Canada hints at possible sanctions, alleging ties between Indian agents and violent activities in Canada. India denies these claims, expelling six Canadian diplomats in retaliation and recalling its high commissioner.
title: Bishnoi wants aapka address…: Viral memes after Canadian PM targets India

description: Xiaomeisha Sea World in Shenzhen faced backlash for showcasing a mechanical whale shark after five years of renovations. Critics highlighted the robot's visible gaps and the high entry fee of $40, expressing disappointment on social media. The aquarium defended the decision, citing laws against trading live whale sharks, but visitors remained dissatisfied.
title: Chinese aquarium criticised for using robot instead of real Whale Shark

description: Kamran Ghulam's century on debut has vindicated Pakistan's decision to drop Babar Azam, drawing praise from former cricketers. Ghulam's 118-run knock under pressure highlighted his capabilities and opened doors for other domestic players. The move, criticized by Michael Vaughan, saw Pakistan reach 259 for 5, with Mohammad Rizwan ensuring stability on day one.
title: 'Mai hoon na': Show Kamran Ghulam's picture to Vaughan, says Basit

description: Kamala Harris promises to legalize recreational marijuana if elected, emphasizing its disproportionate impact on Black men. She aims to work with Congress to ensure lawful cultivation, distribution, and possession of cannabis, and plans to support Black entrepreneurs through forgivable loans and better regulation.
title: 'No jail for smoking weed': Harris promises to legalise marijuana

description: The Karnataka High Court quashed charges against two men accused of shouting ‘Jai Shri Ram' in a mosque, ruling it did not outrage religious feelings. Justice M Nagaprasanna observed there were no grounds for criminal trespass or public mischief, emphasizing that harmony existed between Hindus and Muslims in the area.
title: Karnataka HC: Shouting ‘Jai Shri Ram’ won’t outrage anyone’s religious feelings

description: BJP initiated its new chief's election process with J P Nadda naming a national returning officer and co-returning officers for the organisational vote. The activity will conclude in early next year post state-level polls. Rajya Sabha MP K Laxman, along with co-returning officers Rekha Verma, Sambit Patra, and Naresh Bansal, will oversee the elections.
title: BJP sets in motion process to elect new party chief

description: The United States urged India to cooperate with Canada’s investigation into the killing of Sikh separatist leader Hardeep Singh Nijjar, emphasizing the seriousness of the allegations. Diplomatic tensions have escalated following India's expulsion of Canadian diplomats and concerns over safety amid accusations from Prime Minister Justin Trudeau.
title: 'Extremely serious ... ': What US said on Canada's charge against India

description: Bomb threats on social media disrupted 10 Indian flights over two days, causing diversions and security checks. All threats were hoaxes. Authorities detained two suspects, including a tech-savvy teen. Airlines followed safety protocols, and legal actions are considered. Indian skies remain safe, according to officials.
title: Delhi-Chicago flight diverted to Canada as bomb hoaxes disrupt operations for 2nd day

description: Communal clashes in Bahraich during a Durga idol immersion resulted in the death of a 22-year-old man and injuries to others. Authorities have arrested 52 people and suspended internet services. CM Yogi Adityanath has offered compensation to the victim's family, declaring benefits under PM Awas Yojana.
title: Shops shut, tight vigil in Bahraich; 52 arsonists held

description: Indian government believes Canadian PM Trudeau escalated tensions over Khalistani terrorist Hardeep Singh Nijjar's killing to deflect attention from allegations of failing to prevent China's interference in Canadian politics, doubting Trudeau's accusations against India, and seeking to preserve multifaceted bilateral relations.
title: Did an impending deposition spur Trudeau sabre-rattling?

description: Baba Siddique, a former Congress corporator from Bandra West, saw his political and business fortunes rise along with Mumbai's flourishing real estate market in the late 1990s. Known for his involvement in slum rehabilitation projects, Siddique built a substantial real estate empire with ventures in Mumbai, Dubai, and London.
title: Baba bloomed with realty boom in Bandra

description: Baba Siddique, a politician from NCP, was killed by suspected shooters after multiple failed attempts. The shooters, linked to the Lawrence Bishnoi gang, were given a bike for reconnaissance. The shooting was reportedly a message to actor Salman Khan. Several suspects, including a milk dairy owner, have been arrested. Police plan to invoke stringent charges.
title: Bishnoi gang wanted to convey Salman Khan a message: Probe

description: A report by Policy Exchange highlights the Indian community in Britain as the top-performing ethnic group in professions, pay rates, home ownership, and social integration. Despite high achievements, social class, rather than race, remains the key barrier to success. The rise of 'minorities in towns' is led by aspirational British Indians, shaping future electoral battlegrounds.
title: British Indians most successful ethnic group in UK: report

description: Batting legend Sachin Tendulkar was recently seen with former Pakistan cricket stars Wasim Akram, Zaheer Abbas, and Moin Khan during his visit to the National Cricket League (NCL) in Dallas, USA. The tournament, played in the T10 format, took place at the University of Texas cricket ground's new cricket stadium.
title: Tendulkar enjoys a day with friends from Pakistan - See pic

description: Following a diplomatic crisis between India and Canada, Prime Minister Justin Trudeau sought UK support against alleged targeted campaigns by Indian agents. Trudeau and UK PM Keir Starmer emphasized the rule of law. Numerous incidents of intimidation and violence linked to Indian operatives are reportedly under Canadian investigation.
title: Trudeau seeks support from old ally Britain, pro-Khalistan Sikhs sense opportunity

description: The seat-sharing formula for Maharashtra's assembly polls has not been finalized by either MVA or Mahayuti due to lack of consensus. The MVA has agreed on 230 candidates and expects to finalize the rest soon. Mahayuti is also close to a resolution.
title: Maharashtra polls: No agreement beyond 230 seats within either MVA or Mahayuti

description: Gopal Mishra was murdered during the Bahraich clash, bearing brutal injuries including knife marks, pulled out nails, and pellet wounds. His wife Roli and family demand justice, recounting the horrific details and their ordeal following the incident. Their grief and loss are profound.
title: Bahraich violence: ‘Husband was subjected to torture in last moments’
